The '''Cotton Mill Women's Strikes''' occurred in 1845 through 1848 in [[Allegheny, Pennsylvania|Allegheny City]], now [[Pittsburgh]]. It was an organized effort of the 1,500 women laborers to prevent their employers to force them to work twelve hour work days. It also ended [[Child labour|child labor]] in the mills.<ref>McCollester, Charles and Howard Scott. Labor Historical Sites in the Pittsburgh Region, Allegheny County Labor Council Area Labor Federation, p. 1.</ref>
